com.yantra.interop.japi

Interface YIFXMLAttrOverride

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    YIFXMLAttrOverrideExtn

    public interface YIFXMLAttrOverride
    This interface is used to extend the capabilities of the Defaulting Component. It can be implemented to add additional defaulting logic and to revert selected changes made by the service component.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      org.w3c.dom.Document applyOverrides(YFSEnvironment env, org.w3c.dom.Document originalXML, org.w3c.dom.Document modifiedXML)
      Apply any custom overrides to the input XML.

    • Method Detail

      • applyOverrides

        org.w3c.dom.Document applyOverrides(YFSEnvironment env,
                                    org.w3c.dom.Document originalXML,
                                    org.w3c.dom.Document modifiedXML)
        Apply any custom overrides to the input XML.

        This method will be called by the Defaulting Component after it has applied any other overrides specified during its configuration.

        To ensure consistency, this method should not modify the Document passed in the originalXML parameter. It may safely modify and return the Document in the modifiedXML parameter.

        env Environment handle returned by the createEnvironment API. originalXML The XML document prior to modification by the defaulting engine. modifiedXML The XML document after all other modifications have taken place. The XML document after any custom overrides have taken place.
